Soo excited to partner with @covergirl to bring you this no-makeup makeup look using their new Lash Blast Clean Volume Mascara and the Clean Fresh Collection! You know I like to keep it simple & I love COVERGIRL’s easy breezy aesthetic As a former lash extension fan, my favorite product is the new Lash Blast Clean Mascara I am *very* particular about my mascara because oftentimes they look heavy and thick and I like to keep it natural. This is designed to get every lash and doesn’t get clumpy⁣
or look overdone but it still delivers, and my lashes look long and full- plus it’s vegan & cruelty-free!⁣
⁣
I don’t have any fancy lighting or tricks so this is exactly how the makeup looks IRL, in natural light, and honestly, I love it, I feel fresh-faced and confident. What’s your daily makeup routine?⁣
⁣
#COVERGIRLpartner #COVERGIRLmade #LashBlastClean @ultabeauty

node.text:
I tend to be pretty scientifically minded and gravitate towards things that are black and white; I usually tune out when I hear phrases like “energy work” or “spirit guide.” But this conversation with @kelseyjpatel shifted my perspective and she helped me understand how scientific healing and energy healing can coexist. To be totally honest, I felt a weight lifted after we recorded this; from her guiding me through my perfectionism to our conversation about trauma (we both lost friends to murder) I was able to process and work through things that I normally bottle up inside. ⁣
⁣
On top of all of THAT she gave simple, practical tips that we can all do today to be more present and mindful. Hello, airplane mode! ✈️ if you’re struggling with anxiety, perfectionism, distractedness or trauma, head to @theblondefilespodcast episode 93 to listen! 💗

Do 5 mins of the following:⁣⁣

50 jump ropes⁣⁣
20 lateral hops (10 per side)⁣⁣
20 commando jacks (10 per side)⁣⁣
20 crawl outs⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Repeat 2 - 4 times!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
LMK if you do this! Happy Friday 🥰

Hi hi babes! Here’s an outer thigh burner to add to your workouts this weekend! 🔥 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Repeat 4 times: ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
24 glute kicks (12 per side)⁣⁣
24 side to front kicks (12 per side) ⁣⁣
24 fire hydrants (12 per side)⁣⁣
1 minute of monster walks⁣⁣
24 standing side kicks ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This is effective on its own, or you could add just 2 rounds as a finisher to leg day (good luck 😆🙏🏽) or LISS. Let me know if you’re trying it and have an amazing weekend! xoxo⁣⁣

My friend challenged me to make healthier SNICKERS ICE CREAM BARS and I have to say I nailed it 😏 full disclosure I eyeballed everything but this is my method!⁣ oh and they’re vegan 😍
⁣
INGREDIENTS:⁣
⁣
1 pint vegan vanilla ice cream (I used @craigsla )⁣
2 cups peanuts ⁣
⁣
CARAMEL: ⁣
⁣
1 cup peanut butter ⁣
3/4 cup coconut oil ⁣
3/4 cup maple syrup ⁣
⁣
NOUGAT: (honestly you could omit this and it’d still be amazing)⁣
⁣
1/2 cup almond flour ⁣
1/2 cup coconut flour ⁣
1/2 cup maple syrup ⁣
1/4 cup nut milk⁣
1/2 tsp vanilla ⁣
⁣
CHOCOLATE COATING:⁣
⁣
4 @hukitchen chocolate bars ⁣
sea salt ⁣
⁣
DIRECTIONS:⁣
⁣
*I used a paper loaf pan because it was easy to peel off once everything was frozen so I highly recommend this method! Not sure how it would work in metal⁣
Add ice cream to loaf pan and smooth it down so it’s all even ⁣
Add nougat (if using) and press to pack it down⁣
Add peanuts ⁣
Pour caramel mixture over the top and FREEZE until hard ⁣
Separately, melt chocolate in a pan over low heat (add a few tbsp coconut oil so it doesn’t stick) and pour over frozen ice cream/caramel bar⁣
Freeze again then remove from pan and slice UPSIDE DOWN so starting to cut through the bottom and cutting the top layer last (this prevents the chocolate coating from breaking)⁣
⁣
Who’s gonna try this?! 💖

I’m talking to Dr. Emeran Mayer—world renowned gastroenterologist, neuroscientist and Distinguished Research Professor in the Departments of Medicine, Physiology and Psychiatry at the David Geffen School of Medicine at UCLA—about the gut, the gut-brain connection and how they influence each other. We discuss:⁣
⁣
🧠 why the gut-brain connection is so important⁣
🧠 how emotions and stress affect the gut; anxiety and the gut⁣
🧠 how food fear contributes to digestive issues⁣
🧠 multidisciplinary treatments for IBS⁣
🧠 why digestive issues are so prevalent right now⁣
🧠 what to eat for a healthy gut and so much more⁣
⁣
I’d love to hear your thoughts if you’re listening! x

If you’re looking for a delish summer recipe to make this weekend, these gluten free raw lemon bars are IT 🌼🍋 they’re sweet, tangy and refreshing and could not be easier to make 👌🏻⁣ you can also add food dye or fruit/vegetable juice to make the filling colorful and festive 🇺🇸⁣
⁣⁣
INGREDIENTS:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Crust:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2 cups almond flour ⁣⁣
1/2 cup coconut oil (melted)⁣⁣
1/2 cup maple syrup ⁣⁣
1 tsp vanilla extract ⁣⁣
Pinch of salt ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Filling:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2 cans of coconut milk (refrigerated)⁣⁣
3/4 cup honey ⁣⁣
3/4 - 1 cup fresh lemon juice ⁣⁣
3 tbsp arrowroot ⁣powder⁣
Lemon zest, powdered sugar to garnish ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
DIRECTIONS:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
For crust, combine ingredients and pour into a lined square pan (I used 8”)⁣⁣
Preheat oven to 350 Fahrenheit ⁣⁣
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned ⁣⁣
(ovens may vary)⁣⁣
Remove and let cool ⁣⁣
For filling, scoop the hardened part out of chilled cans of coconut milk and add to blender; add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth ⁣⁣
Pour over cooled crust and freeze until hard⁣⁣
Garnish with lemon zest and powdered sugar ⁣⁣
*you can keep it in the fridge or freezer ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Lmk if you’re going to try! x
